commitResults.messageTitle: Finished Level-1 increment with some personality modification for my chat bot
Add a class Task to handle more complex logics involving a Task
Finished Level-3 Incrementing: Mark as Done Handled basic error inputs such as index out of bounds on ArrayList of Tasks
Level-4-Part-1: Created a Deadline.java file, handled Deadline task logics. Corrected indentation of console text outputs.

Level-4-part-1-Update: Handle Deadline Task in Deadline.java file instead of Duke.java This is to practice calling Class Methods and writing neater code. Consider if there are 100 different types of tasks. It is not good to implement Task handling modules all in Duke.java file. It is way neater to implement task handling in each of the specific types of Task.
Level-4-Part-2: Added Todo.java and handling a Todo Task.
Level-4-Part-3: Added Event.java file and its logics
A-TextUiTesting: Text Formatting correction To prepare for automated testing
A-TextUiTesting: Update input.txt and EXPECTED.TEXT\ To match predetermined results for outputs

A-TextUiTesting: Use dos2unix input.txt This is because ACTUAL.TXT and EXPECTED.TXT look the same to naked eye The issue might lie in line-ending differences hence troubleshooting with dos2unix solved the issue. OS: Windows 11
Level-5: Add two classes to handle two types of exceptions Handled basic erroneous inputs of empty todo description and Invalid command. Might be exploring Enumeration to handle Invalid command
Level-5-Update-1: Updated Duke.java and Todo.java To throw the two new exceptions appropriately: EmptyDescriptionException and InvalidCommandException

Level-6: Added deleteTask() function in Duke.java Also added exception checkings on user inputs such as empty description, invalid index, or non-integer index. Might explore creating Custom Exception Class in the future.
Level-6-Update: Small corrections of coding styles
Bug fix: "todo todo" was read as no descriptions because initial implementation wiped out ALL todo's. Same issue for Deadline and Event objects. Fixed with replaceFirst() instead of replace()
A-Enum: Applied Enum on available commands and used switch-case instead of if-else. To make code more expandable.
